        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[<blockquote>
<p>Relevance is the most important factor in directing your learning.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is a theory I have been cooking up for about the past three days. The entire premise is that without relevance, it&rsquo;s entirely impossible to learn effectively, let alone <em>learn</em>.</p>
<p>So let&rsquo;s define relevance within this context.</p>
<h2 id="relevance">Relevance</h2>
<p>Relevance is essentially the <em>metadata</em> attached to your present learning situation. Metadata describes how the data is structured, what it contains and how it&rsquo;s used. This is from the perspective of computing.</p>]]></summary>
    </entry>
